Dear all\cb1 \
\cb3 As a reminder before the next class on 
\f1\b 8th April
\f0\b0 , you are expected to submit your model results (aka system runs) to our shared Github repository: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26}}\cb1 \
\cb3 We have prepared an updated version of our Austrian Tax dataset, which you should use as input to your models (only as a test set, don't fine-tune on this data): {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/blob/main/dataset_clean.csv"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/blob/main/dataset_clean.csv }}Your submission files should look like this example\'a0(format CSV with , delimiter, id of the question and answer of your model): {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/blob/main/sample_model_output.csv"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/blob/main/sample_model_output.csv }}but for all questions in the dataset, i.e., 644 rows as in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/blob/main/dataset_clean.csv"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 dataset_clean.csv }}Submit a separate CSV file for each of your models.\cb1 \
\cb3 Every student is invited to submit results and code for 3 models:\cb1 \
\cb3 1) Inference only (use an existing model from a library or through an API)
\f1\b  +5pt
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\cb3 2) Fine-tune models (getting training data is up to you, recommended to use a library to fine-tune your models on GoogleColab or Kaggle free notebooks) 
\f1\b +5pt
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\cb3 3) RAG (improve your LLM by adding a retrieval model to provide relevant passages, e.g., from the legal documents that we used to create the dataset) 
\f1\b +5pt
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\cb3 You are encouraged to experiment and submit the results of the best models. The submission that achieves best performance will receive 
\f1\b +20pt
\f0\b0  in the end (only submissions with three runs are considered and the scores are averaged across all three runs)\cb1 \
\cb3 Results without the code available to reproduce them will not be considered.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'a0\cb1 \

\f1\b \cb3 GitHub instructions
\f0\b0 . Check GitHub_Tutorial_v2.ipynb on Canvas for details on how to use GitHub. Your submission should appear here before the class starts as a pull request: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/pulls"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 https://github.com/svakulenk0/wu-llms-ss26/pulls}} Add your model results and the code you used to generate those results in a separate folder, e.g., Team1/code/.. and \'a0Team1/results/ Do not modify any of the existing files or add new files outside of your team folder. Teams are allowed to have a shared folder with shared source code but every team member has to submit their own model results that differ from other team members' submissions not only by hyper-parameters but also by the models used.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'a0\cb1 \
